column5: You know the ice is thick when it's getting measured in quarter inches...LOL  Looks like you had another slay day.  nice goin'
Looks like you were pretty lonely out there , it won't be like that for very much longer . Nice lakers , keep them coming
Good fishing!!  Thanks for the report.
Nice going Steve!!! 3 3/4" huh? I drilled through 44" today!! Didn't have much in the way of luck though.
Nice bunch of fish man, well done!
you ice fishing guys are a special breed i tell ya ....great report though!....you wouldnt catch me ALIVE out there
And if you're going to go out on thin ice please take safety equipment. Jim Hudson a Lake Superior guide died today when he went through the ice while guiding.
Wasnt that lonely, I just trekked away from the pack.  The pack was out in full force this weekend though!!
Simcoe laker and whitey reports are always a treat.  Good fishing Steve.
